# Pull request watch (reviewgate-core)

When the user cares about PRs, CI, or merging, **do not assume** there are no open PRs.

There is **no** automated code review in CI; reviews must be grounded in the actual diff.

1. Run: `gh pr list --repo leo-aa88/reviewgate-core --state open --json number,title,url`
2. For each open PR, fetch the diff (`gh pr diff <number> --repo leo-aa88/reviewgate-core`) and review against project standards: strict typing (no silent `Any`), Google-style docstrings on public APIs, file size (non-test under 500 LOC preferred, max 600), modularity, no compat fallbacks without agreement, no magic literals without names, correctness and tests, concurrency safety, KISS/DRY, SOLID/clean code.
3. Post **at most one** substantive comment per PR via `gh pr comment`: tie feedback to **specific files/hunks** (or cite diff context), list concrete change requests or approve with reasons. Do **not** post generic checklist-only comments that ignore the patch.

If `gh` is unavailable or the user is not authenticated, say so and stop after listing what you would have checked.
